About=I am a Perl script running under Irssi. I am open source: https://github.com/neilhwatson/cfbot See Help for more info.
Best Practices=CFEngine best practices: http://evolvethinking.com/category/cfengine/best-practices/ and https://github.com/atsaloli/cf-health-check 
Bugs=CFEngine bug and feature request tracker: https://dev.cfengine.com/projects/core/activity
DH=Delta Hardening is an open source data pack for EFL. DH provides ready to use host hardening policy based on NSA and NIST recommendations. http://evolvethinking.com/products/delta_hardening/, https://github.com/evolvethinking/evolve_cfengine_freelib/tree/3.5/policy_data/delta_hardening
DR=Delta Reporting is an open source policy compliance and reporting tool for CFEngine. https://github.com/evolvethinking/delta_reporting
EFL=The Evolve Free Library is an open source, production ready CFEngine policy framework. https://github.com/evolvethinking/evolve_cfengine_freelib
Frameworks=NCF and EFL are two third party policy frameworks for CFEngine. Both are designed to help users get more work done in a shorter time frame. See EFL and NCF for more information.
Help=Usage: !cfbot <keyword> I am case insensitive.
NCF=NCF s a framework that runs in pure CFEngine language, to help structure your CFEngine policy and provide reusable, single purpose components distributed under the GPLv3 license. http://www.ncf.io 
Rudder=Rudder is an easy to use, web-driven, role-based solution for IT Infrastructure Automation and Compliance. It runs on CFEengine. http://www.rudder-project.org/site/
Support=Third party CFEngine consultants: http://www.verticalsysadmin.com/cfengine/ps.htm
